### 7. Test Documentation

**`/Users/4thwithme/Documents/repo/recommendations-service/test/CLAUDE.md`**
- HTTP test pattern using supertest and `request(getHttpServer).get(endpoint)`
- Controller tests without HTTP server using `Test.createTestingModule()`
- Mocking strategy: inline mock providers (most common) or `.overrideProvider()`
- Coverage requirements: 95% minimum (branches, functions, lines, statements)
- E2E test scope: REST endpoints, full module integration, DB operations, cache behavior
- Database: test DB is MySQL replica, reset runs automatically before e2e
- Excluded from coverage: load-test, newrelic, algolia, mms, bigquery, cli, style-copurchases, color-match-worker

**`/Users/4thwithme/Documents/repo/recommendations-service/src/unit-tests/CLAUDE.md`**
- Unit test scope: utilities, service layer, decorators, models, configs
- Mocking pattern: always use `Test.createTestingModule` with `useValue` providers
- Test structure: describe -> methodName -> should behavior when condition
- Coverage: 95% minimum is NON-NEGOTIABLE
- Every branch must be covered: if/else, ternaries, optional chaining, error paths
- `/modules/db/` excluded from unit coverage
- Logger spying pattern for assertion without noise

