### 8. npm Scripts for Running Tests

From `package.json`:

```bash
npm run test:unit              # Run unit tests only
npm run test:e2e              # Run e2e tests with db:reset
npm run test:unit:coverage    # Unit tests with 95% coverage enforcement
npm run test:e2e:coverage     # E2E tests with 95% coverage enforcement
npm run test                  # Run code-quality-check + unit & e2e in parallel
npm run test:coverage         # Full coverage suite for both

npm run db:reset:test         # Reset test database manually
```

All test commands use `dotenv -e .env.test` to load test environment variables.

